Amazon VPC

VPC- Virtual private cloud
is a private network to deploy resources

subnets: sub-division inside vpc
public: has route to Internet Gateway- access to internet
private: dont have access to internet

Route tables: defines access to internet & subnet

Internet Gateway: helps VPC instances to connect to internet
NAT Gateway: helps private subnets to connect to internet, while beign private


Network ACL: is like a firewall to subnets
-> have allow & deney rules
-> rules include only ip address
Security Groups: firewall to EC2 instance
-> have allow rules
-> include both ip address & other security groups


VPC Flow Logs:
capture info about VPC, subnets, lastic Network Interface
vpc low logs data goes to s3 & cloud watch logs.


VPC Peeering:
private connection btw 2 VPC
->no transitive peering

VPC Endpoints:
allow private access to AWS without using internet
used to avoid gateways(internet & nat), ip address
Endpoint Gateway:s3 & DynamoDB
Endpoint Instance: all services

AWS privatelink:
private secure connection
requires Network load balancer, Elastic Network Interface

Site to Site VPN:
-> connect on-primises to aws
-> automatically encrypted
-> over  public internet
-> must use Customer gateway

Direct Connect:
-> physical connection btw on-premises & aws
-> over private network
-> must use virtual private gateway

Transit gateway:
-> allow transit peering


